🔹 How It Works
Step 1 — Development

You created a Vite React app.

Locally:

npm run dev

Runs on:

http://localhost:3000
Step 2 — Production Build

Inside Dockerfile (frontend):

Stage 1:

node:20-alpine
npm install
npm run build

This generates:

/dist folder

Stage 2:

nginx:alpine
COPY dist → /usr/share/nginx/html

So now:

Nginx serves static files

No Node runtime needed in production

Lightweight image

This is called:

👉 Multi-stage Docker build

