🗄 3️⃣ Database Setup (PostgreSQL in Container)

You are NOT running DB on your local machine.

Instead:

Docker is running:

postgres:15

Inside docker-compose:

services:
  db:
    image: postgres:15
    environment:
      POSTGRES_USER: postgres
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: postgres
      POSTGRES_DB: mydb

This creates:

isolated database container

internal docker network

no need to install Postgres locally

🔗 4️⃣ How FE → BE → DB Connection Works

This is very important.

🧠 Docker Networking Explained

When you run:

docker compose up

Docker creates:

default network

All services join that network:

frontend

backend

db

They can talk using service names.

🔹 Backend to Database Connection

Inside backend .env:

DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@db:5432/mydb

Notice:

@db

Not:

localhost

Because:

Inside container,
localhost means that container itself.

So backend connects to:

db (postgres container)

via Docker internal DNS.

🔹 Frontend to Backend Connection

Right now:

Frontend calls:

http://localhost:5000

Because:

browser runs on your machine

backend is exposed via:

ports:
  - "5000:5000"

So mapping works:

Host Machine → Container
